{
  "texts": [
    "However, the standard deviation for NetLogo is around 20, whereas LLM displays a much lower standard deviation of about 7.",
    "In contrast, the Hybrid model outperforms the other two variants, collecting an average of approximately 95 units of food with a standard deviation of about 12.",
    "This superior performance is due to the combination of the behavioural differences between LLM-guided ants and rule-based ants.",
    "The zoomed inset in Figure 3, for example, shows that Hybrid starts returning food to the nest at around 20 simulation steps, whereas LLM and NetLogo begin this process at about 40 steps.",
    "This means that, for some reason, the Hybrid variant is more efficient in quickly finding food sources."
  ]
}